x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Journal of Inorganic and Nuclear Chemistry, Vol.30, p.2891 (1968)

x4freetext: The target assembly consisted of thin approximately
10 mg/cm**2 highly enriched Pb-208 foils (99.3%),
surrounded by 0.001-inch aluminum catcher foils of
high purity followed on either side by 0.001-inch
aluminum monitor foils and wrapped with 0.001-inch
aluminum. The dimensions of the aluminum foils were
1*1 inch and overlapped the target foils whose
dimensions were 0.75*0.75 inch.
The results are compared with similar data
previously obtained for U-238.
A Gaussion charge distribution.
The recoil data have been used to derive, for a
given mass chain, the dependence on atomic number of
the average cascade deposition energy, the average
total kinetic energy release and the average separation
distance between the primary fragment charge centers.
Methane-flow proportional counter for the
measurements of the Na-24 activity.
Several end-window methane flow proportional counters
in the case of the negatron emitters, Ag-111, Ag-112,
A 3*3 in. sodium iodide crystal in the case of
the In-111. A thin NAICR connected to a single channel
analyzer in the measurement of the X-ray activity of
